# Code Style Guidelines

## Formatting Standards

- Use Prettier defaults (2-space indent, double quotes, trailing commas where valid, semicolons on).
- Run `pnpm lint` (includes formatting/lint rules); keep imports ordered.

## Naming Conventions

- Variables/functions: `camelCase`, descriptive (avoid abbreviations).
- Constants: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` (object constants `as const`).
- Types/interfaces/classes: `PascalCase`; component props suffix `Props`.
- Files/folders: kebab-case for folders/utilities; components in `PascalCase` files.

## Import Organization

- Order: external → internal aliases (`@/`) → relative.
- Use aliases instead of deep relatives.
- Use `import type` for type-only imports; remove unused imports.

## Error Handling

- Prefer explicit errors with context; avoid silent failures.
- Use custom error types where helpful; log with actionable info.

## Function Structure & Best Practices

- Small, focused functions; required params first.
- Prefer `const`; extract complex logic into helpers/hooks.
- Keep TS strict; avoid `any`; use `cn` for conditional classes and avoid nested ternaries in JSX.

## TypeScript & React Basics

- Props use interfaces with `Props` suffix; prefer string literal unions over enums and use `as const` for literal inference.
- Use `import type` for type-only imports; keep value and type imports separate when possible.
- Default to server components; gate browser-only logic with mounted checks to prevent hydration drift.
- Keep components lean and declarative; lift state to hooks/Zustand selectors; favor immutable updates.
